          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-03-26T22:11:35Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Revolving Door Pension Prevention Act </strong></p> <p>Prohibits any former Member of Congress who is a registered lobbyist who receives&nbsp;annual&nbsp;compensation of $1 million or more for lobbying activities from receiving&nbsp; benefits under: (1) the Civil Service Retirement System or the Federal Employees' Retirement System (including the Thrift Savings Plan); or (2) the Federal Employees Health Benefits Program (including enhanced dental or vision benefits).</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2015-01-27T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
